<?xml version="1.0"?>
<package xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <metadata>
    <id>calibre</id>
    <title>Calibre</title>
    <version>0.9.16</version>
    <authors>Kovid Goyal</authors>
    <owners>Gary Ewan Park</owners>
    <summary>calibre is the one stop solution to all your e-book needs.</summary>
    <description>calibre is a free and open source e-book library management application developed by users of e-books for users of e-books.</description>
    <projectUrl>http://calibre-ebook.com/</projectUrl>
    <tags>ebook library management</tags>
    <copyright>Kovid Goyal</copyright>
    <licenseUrl>http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html</licenseUrl>
    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/gep13/ChocolateyPackages/raw/master/calibre/calibre.ico</iconUrl>
    <releaseNotes>
    - New: News download: Add support for logging in to sites that require javascript for their logins.
    - New: News download: Do not convert all downloaded images to JPG format. This fixes the problem of PNG images with transparent backgrounds being rendered with black backgrounds
    - New: CHM Input: Support hierarchical table of contents. Do not generate an inline table of contents when a metadata table of contents is present. Also correctly decode the text in the table of contents
	- New: Get Books: Add the beam-ebooks.de store
	- New: Make custom yes/no columns using icons put text values under the icons.
	- New: Driver for LG E400 and SayCoolA710
	- New: Speed up device connection when there are lots of books on the device by not generating cover thumbnails unless they are actually needed.
	- New: Have the metadata download dialog remember its last used size.
    - Fixed: Fix deleting a custom column that was used in a column coloring rule makes the column coloring preferences panel unusable
    - Fixed: Store caches outside the config directory for non-portable calibre installs
    - Fixed: PDF Output: Dont crash if the user has a font on his system that is missing the OS/2 table
    - Fixed: Conversion: Do not error out because of an error in user supplied search replace rules.
    - Fixed: Conversion: Replace all non-ascii characters in CSS class names, as they cause problems with some broken EPUB renderers.
    - Fixed: Do not choke when reading metadata from MOBI files with incorrectly encoded metadata fields
    - Fixed: Conversion: Preserve ToC entries that point nowhere instead of causing them to point to a non-existent file
    - Fixed: E-book viewer: Allow entries in the Table of Contents that do not point anywhere, instead of just ignoring them.
	- Fixed: Content server: Fix the 'Previous' link in the mobile version of the content server webpage skipping an entry
	- New News Source: Contemporary Argentine Writers by Darko Miletic
    - Improved News Source: TSN
    - Improved News Source: St. Louis Post Dispatch
    - Improved News Source: Metro UK
    - Improved News Source: Michelle Malkin
    - Improved News Source: Barrons
    </releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
</package>
